SIMPLE: rigid
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Rigid
<hw>Rig"id</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>rigidus</ets>,
fr. <ets>rigere</ets> to be stiff or numb: cf. F. <ets>rigide</ets>. Cf.
<er>Rigor</er>. ]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Firm; stiff; unyielding; not
pliant; not flexible.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Upright beams innumerable⟦br⟧
Of <qex>rigid</qex> spears.</q> <rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Hence, not lax or indulgent; severe; inflexible;
strict; <as>as, a <ex>rigid</ex> father or master; <ex>rigid</ex>
discipline; <ex>rigid</ex> criticism; <ex>a rigid</ex>
sentence.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The more <qex>rigid</qex> order of principles in religion and
government.</q> <rj><qau>Hawthorne.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Stiff; unpliant; inflexible; unyielding; strict;
exact; severe; austere; stern; rigorous; unmitigated.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Rigidity</ent>⟦br⟧
